+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SrEyXiVcwFa3YUVXkKsAau","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No checkpoints found. The project is set up with TypeScript, Vitest, ESLint — just needs the implementation in `src/`.\n\nNon-interactive mode: using Autopilot.\n\nLet me work through the design decisions for this constraint-based event scheduler.\n\n**Q: What algorithm approach for constraint satisfaction?**\n→ Choosing: **Greedy with backtracking-lite (priority-based scheduling with room swapping)**\n  Reasoning: A full CSP solver (like arc consistency + backtracking) is overkill. A pure greedy approach won't maximize scheduled events. A priority-based greedy approach that considers event difficulty (fewer valid placements = higher priority) combined with the ability to try multiple room/time combinations gives good results without excessive complexity. We topologically sort by prerequisites, then schedule hardest-to-place events first.\n\n**Q: How to handle topological ordering with prerequisite chains?**\n→ Choosing: **Kahn's algorithm (BFS-based topological sort)**\n  Reasoning: Clean cycle detection (if not all nodes are visited, there's a cycle), straightforward implementation, and naturally produces a valid ordering.\n\n**Q: Data structure for tracking room availability?**\n→ Choosing: **Sorted interval list per room**\n  Reasoning: Simple array of occupied time slots per room, checked for overlap + gap constraints. With typical event counts (< thousands), linear scan per room is fast enough and keeps the code simple.\n\n**Q: How to maximize scheduled events?**\n→ Choosing: **Priority scheduling by \"most constrained first\" heuristic**\n  Reasoning: Schedule events that have the fewest valid room options first (small capacity rooms, strict prerequisites). This is a well-known heuristic from constraint satisfaction that maximizes placements without exponential search.\n\n**Q: Architecture — single file or modular?**\n→ Choosing: **Two files: types in `src/types.ts`, logic in `src/scheduler.ts`, re-exported from `src/index.ts`**\n  Reasoning: Clean separation of concerns without over-engineering.\n\nNow let me write the design document and proceed to implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1087,"cache_read_input_tokens":21952,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1087},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19d32348-d71b-4c21-a504-e0597227717d","uuid":"b8370ef4-b0b1-4f44-a912-54534f8b5baa"}
